文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_031_chunk3
证据片段: Before irradiation, twinning occurred in the uniformly deformed region of T specimens of all materials. The amount of twinning tended to increase with grain size, and to decrease with increasing alloy content.

文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_031_chunk3
证据片段: Bement [8] found previously that twinning was not markedly changed by irradiation

文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_031_chunk3
证据片段: After irradiation at 575 K the specimens of BY material exhibited large amounts of uniform elongation for both crystallographic textures

文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_031_chunk3
证据片段: In deformed sections of the specimens there were cleared swaths which did not have any defects

文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_031_chunk3
证据片段: In some twins in uniformly deformed material there were many irradiation induced defects

文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_031_chunk3
证据片段: in others no defects could be seen even when the foil was tilted for maximum contrast in the twin

文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_031_chunk3
证据片段: This behavior seems to be different from that of irradiated annealed rhenium [9], where damage was always found in the twins

文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_031_chunk3
证据片段: for most irradiated zirconium alloys tested at ≤ 575 K, the strain rate sensitivity is small

证据片段: irradiated fuel sheathing of annealed Zr-Nb alloy should undergo more circumferential strain before onset of plastic instability than sheathing of annealed Zircaloy

文献ID: STP551-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_2nd Volume_031_chunk4
证据片段: Niobium additions to zirconium promote plastic stability in irradiated material
